Sentencas: A cubic perovskite oxide, BaBi0.05Co0.8Nb0.15O3-delta (BBCN) is investigated as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Novel BaBi0.05Co0.8Nb0.15O3-δ perovskite oxide as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: XRD results show that BBCN cathode is chemically compatible with the electrolyte Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) at 950 degrees C for 5 h. The XPS results show that the Co3+/Co4+, Nb5+, Bi3+ and Ba2+ species exist in the BBCN sample.
Titulo: Novel BaBi0.05Co0.8Nb0.15O3-δ perovskite oxide as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) of the BBCN sample is 19.60 x 10(-6) K-1 between 30 and 850 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Novel BaBi0.05Co0.8Nb0.15O3-δ perovskite oxide as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The R-p of BBCN cathode on SDC electrolyte is 0.047, 0.077 and 0.136 Omega cm(2) at 800, 750, 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Novel BaBi0.05Co0.8Nb0.15O3-δ perovskite oxide as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A maximum power density of 507 mW cm(-2) is obtained at 800 degrees C for single-cell with 300 mu m thick SDC electrolyte and BBCN cathode.
Titulo: Novel BaBi0.05Co0.8Nb0.15O3-δ perovskite oxide as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results of this study demonstrate that BBCN can be a promising cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Novel BaBi0.05Co0.8Nb0.15O3-δ perovskite oxide as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
